tafsir[8]{c,v,t}:
  77,21,"I then put that contemptuous fluid into a safe place i.e. the woman’s womb."
  77,25,"Did I not make the earth capable of holding all the people?"
  77,29,"It will be said to those who rejected whatever their Messengers brought: “O rejectors! Walk to the punishment you used to reject.”"
  77,33,"It is as if the sparks that it spits out are black mountains in their darkness and size."
  77,35,"This is a day on which they will not speak at all."
  77,36,"Neither will they be given permission to present excuses to their Lord for their disbelief and evils."
  77,38,"This is the day of separation between the creations; I have gathered you and the previous nations on one plain."
  77,42,"And among fruits they desire to eat."